  <title>Installing</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Installing PDF Chemistry</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <prereq id="prereq_u24_q3n_vz">
      <p id="p_q45_dgk_54b">
        <note type="other" othertype="Prerequisite" id="note_r45_dgk_54b"><ph keyref="product"/> is a Java application and
          requires the following Oracle Java version, depending on your operating system:<ul
            id="ul_tyh_5sq_skb">
            <li id="li_s45_dgk_54b" irina="irina"><b>Windows</b> or <b>Linux</b> - Java JRE version <ph keyref="currentJavaVersion"
              />.</li>
            <li id="li_t45_dgk_54b" irina="irina"><b>macOS</b> - Java JDK version <ph keyref="currentJavaVersion"/>.</li>
          </ul></note>
      </p>
    </prereq>
    <context id="section_hq3_h3n_vz">
      <p id="p_u45_dgk_54b">To install <ph keyref="product"/> on your platform, follow this procedure:</p>
    </context>
    <steps>
      <step>
        <cmd>Download the distribution for your particular platform from the <term>Oxygen</term>
          website: <xref href="https://oxygenxml.com/pdf_chemistry/download.html" format="html"
            scope="external"/>.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Follow the instructions provided on that web page.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Add the full path for that folder to your PATH environment variable (for information
          about how to do this, see the related links below, depending on your operating
          system).</cmd>
      </step>
			<step>
        <cmd>If you purchased the product, place the license key in the installation directory. The
          name of this file should be <filepath>licensekey.txt</filepath>. Note that unlicensed <ph
            keyref="product"/> produces watermarked output.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Test the installation by typing the following command in a console:</cmd>
        <info>
          <p id="p_v45_dgk_54b"><b>Windows:</b><codeblock outputclass="language-ini" id="codeblock_w45_dgk_54b">chemistry -v</codeblock></p>
          <p id="p_x45_dgk_54b"><b>macOS or
            Linux:</b><codeblock outputclass="language-ini" id="codeblock_y45_dgk_54b">sh chemistry.sh -v</codeblock></p>
          <p id="p_z45_dgk_54b"><b>Result:</b> It should display the version.</p>
        </info>
      </step>
    </steps>
